When the user asks to "store", "save", "capture", or otherwise record something as a note *without specifying a destination*, default to placing it in `inbox/`.

## Inbox note creation rules

- Create a new markdown file under `inbox/` for each captured item.
- Prefer filenames in the form: `YYYY-MM-DD--<slug>.md` (lowercase, hyphen-separated).
- The note should start with:
  - A clear `# Title`
  - A `Date: YYYY-MM-DD` line
  - Optional `Tags:` line
  - The captured content, formatted cleanly

## Index maintenance (required)

Any time you add a new note under `inbox/`, you MUST update `inbox/index.md` in the same change:

- Add a new bullet at the top under “Entries (newest first)”
- The entry must include:
  - Date (ISO `YYYY-MM-DD`)
  - A markdown link to the new note
  - A 1–2 line summary
  - Optional tags (if present in the note)

If you do not create a new inbox note, do not edit the inbox index.
